article.description: — Sam Griffin had 19 points as Tulsa easily beat Alcorn State 83-62 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Griffin scores 19 to carry Tulsa over Alcorn State 83-62
article.linkText: Griffin scores 19 to carry Tulsa over Alcorn State 83-62
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- — Sam Griffin had 19 points as Tulsa easily beat Alcorn State 83-62 on Thursday night. Jeriah Horne had 15 points for Tulsa (6-5). Tim Dalger added 13 points and Curtis Haywood II had 12 points. Paul King scored a season-high 21 points for the Braves (1-9), who have now lost four consecutive games. Oddyst Walker added 16 points. Darrious Agnew had 12 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
